date.headline: Indian Shares Poised For Higher Start On Hopes Of Fed Action
date.text: Indian shares are set to open higher on Thursday after the minutes from the July 31-August 1 Fed meeting showed more stimulus could be on the way.

date.headline: Reliance Power, China Datang to Develop Energy Projects
date.text: Reliance Power Ltd. (532939.BY) has signed an initial agreement with China Datang Corp. to develop and operate power and other energy projects in India and overseas, the latest in a series of deals which the Mumbai-based power producer has signed with companies in Beijing in recent years.

date.headline: Indian River County aces manual audit of primary election
date.text: The Primary Election Canvassing Board met Wednesday to conduct the post-election manual audit of the Aug. 14 primary election, as required by Florida law.

date.headline: India sets up investment panel as FDI slumps 78% in June
date.text: India's government on Friday set up a panel to suggest ways to improve the climate for doing business in the country as figures showed foreign direct investment in India slid by 78 percent in June.

date.headline: Medals honor black Marines who endured segregation to serve
date.text: Montford Point Marines receive Congressional Gold Medal for World War II service John Steele will receive one of the nation's highest civilian awards today — a recognition that almost 70 years ago, he endured segregation to serve his country.

date.headline: Kellie Pickler heading to Indian Ranch
date.text: Although Kellie Pickler is undoubtedly a Southern woman with a perky voice and accent that might make one think of a younger Dolly Parton (one of her idols), the country singer and "American Idol" finalist will be very close to home when she performs at Indian Ranch in Webster on Sunday.

date.text: Ohio businessman Steve Cohen will speak at the Republican National Convention. "Things may never be the way they were," says Cohen, who runs a manufacturing company. "We're going to have to discover new ways to make money."

date.headline: Indian solar hit by climate financing
date.text: NEW DELHI, Aug. 20 (UPI) -- The United States is using climate finance funds to kill India's solar power industry, says an Indian public interest research and advocacy group.

date.headline: India Holds Back Clearances for 52 Oil, Gas Blocks
date.text: India is holding back clearances for more than a fifth of the exploratory blocks it has auctioned in various rounds since 1999 to domestic and overseas energy explorers due to defense, environmental and maritime boundary issues.

date.headline: Bond-Quota Sales Fail as Pimco Frets on Inflation: India Credit
date.text: India fell short of its target at a seventh straight sale of permits to buy rupee bonds and existing quotas are underutilized by global funds on concern the fastest inflation among the biggest emerging markets will accelerate.

date.headline: Singapore Rich Seen Luring Issuers After IDBI Bond: India Credit
date.text: IDBI Bank Ltd. (IDBI) ’s record Singapore- dollar bond sale will prompt more Indian companies to tap increasing demand from wealthy private investors, the city’s top underwriter said.
